<!-- pm/HANDOFF.md — agent-to-agent handoff. Terse by design: fragments over sentences, pointers
     over prose. Overwrite on every handoff. Omit any empty section. NO SECRETS — pm/ is tracked;
     reference locations, never values. -->
# HANDOFF <YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM>

OBJECTIVE: <one line>
PHASE: <phase> · SCALE: <scale> · SIGNED_OFF: <no | yes — <name>, <date>>
POSITION: sprint <n>/<N> · story <id> "<title>" — <status> · verification: <pending|PASS|FAIL|UNKNOWN>

BRANCH: <current> · INTEGRATION: <branch> · UNCOMMITTED: <none | paths>
GATES: test=`<cmd|N/A>` lint=`<cmd|N/A>` build=`<cmd|N/A>`
LAST_GATE_RESULTS: <e.g. test PASS 2026-07-05 · lint N/A · build PASS>

READ_FIRST: <ordered, minimal — e.g. docs/stories/S2-1-*.md, docs/plan.md#commands>
SKIP: <looks relevant but isn't — spare the next agent the tokens>

DONE_THIS_RUN:
- <story/step — outcome, merge commit/PR>

IN_FLIGHT:
- <story id — exactly where it stopped: built/not-built, which gate/review round, what remains>

OPEN_FINDINGS: <none | reviewer findings not yet fixed, severity + file>

DECISIONS (made this run, not yet in docs):
- <decision — why — where it belongs (spec/plan/story/constitution)>

GOTCHAS:
- <trap the next agent will hit — how to avoid it>

BLOCKERS:
- <blocker — what/who it waits on>

NEXT (ordered):
1. <concrete step — file/command>
2. <...>
